{
  "article_id": "SantaBarbaraNewsPress1939",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "An almost-forgotten story of ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "an early day female Robinson Crusoe",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " who for 18 years braved the loneliness of rock-bound ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicholas island",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " off ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara's coast",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_socalcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " was revived yesterday with the return of an expedition from the ",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Channel islands",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          8
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Arthur Woodward",
        "entity_key": "awo",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", director of history and anthropology of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Los Angeles museum",
        "entity_key": "mu_lacountymuseum",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", said there the expedition apparently located the site of the hut occupied by "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indian woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who later was baptized at the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara Old Mission",
        "entity_key": "mi_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " as Juana Maria."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " was left alone on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " in 1835, by "
      },
      {
        "text": "an expedition",
        "entity_keys": [
          "1835crew",
          "chu",
          "isp",
          "iwi",
          "jsjo",
          "jdy",
          "lbu",
          "natam_hawaiian",
          "nativeamericans"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " that had been sent from "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " to remove "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " from "
      },
      {
        "text": "the place",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Just as "
      },
      {
        "text": "the boat",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " was being loaded with "
      },
      {
        "text": "Indians",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " and a storm approached, "
      },
      {
        "text": "Juana Maria",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " ran from the gathering, scampered up the hills, and cried she had forgotten "
      },
      {
        "text": "her baby",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The expedition",
        "entity_keys": [
          "1835crew",
          "chu",
          "isp",
          "iwi",
          "jsjo",
          "jdy",
          "lbu",
          "natam_hawaiian",
          "nativeamericans"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " was forced to depart because of the storm, and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Juana Maria",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " was soon forgotten. For 18 years she lived alone on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Woodward",
        "entity_key": "awo",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " said. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Her baby",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " died meanwhile. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " lived by fishing and hunting with snares."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "In 1853, an expedition headed by ",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "George Nidever",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          14
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " of ",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          14
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " visited ",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          14
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " and captured ",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the half-wild woman",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          14
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who could speak the language only of ",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her tribe",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          14
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", all of whom were then dead. She died six weeks later and was buried at the ",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara mission",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          14
        ],
        "entity_key": "mi_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          14
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Woodward",
        "entity_key": "awo",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " said the expedition returning today also had found what appeared to be the \"mint\" of early-day "
      },
      {
        "text": "California",
        "entity_key": "st_cal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". On "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Cruz",
        "entity_key": "i_scruz",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Rosa",
        "entity_key": "i_sr",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "islands, he said, he found 1,700 fine stone drills used to make beads, which served as the currency for the early day "
      },
      {
        "text": "Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_chumash",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Santa Rosa",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sr",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", ",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Cruz",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_scruz",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", ",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicholas",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " and ",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Miguel",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sm",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " islands were visited during which nearly 200 village sites were inspected and from which relics were obtained, ",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Woodward",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ],
        "entity_key": "awo",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " said.",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "This ever fascinating story of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Juana Maria",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " is to be told and portions of it dramatized over "
      },
      {
        "text": "KTMS",
        "entity_key": "ktms",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " at 7 o'clock tonight."
      }
    ]
  ]
}